{{Info
|body = 


Standard syntax-highlight for codeblocks.

}}


<syntaxhighlight lang="php"><?php

function fetchUser($id) {
    if (!is_numeric($id)) {
        return null;
    }

    $users = [
        1 => "Alice",
        2 => "Bob",
        3 => "Charlie"
    ];

    return $users[$id] ?? null;
}

$userId = 2;
$user = fetchUser($userId);

echo $user ? "User: $user" : "User not found";
</syntaxhighlight>
__NOTOC__

 <!-- From bodyContent 853573636.mraw -->

{{Info |body =
Not available in Confluence cloud editor. Replaced by macro “[[Migration:Macros/Supported_macros/expand|expand]].”
}}
The '''detailssummary''' macro was part of Confluence’s old/legacy editor and allowed you to create a collapsible section with a summary line. In the new Confluence Cloud editor, this macro was removed and replaced by the '''expand''' macro, which provides the same functionality in a modernized form. __NOTOC__
<!-- From bodyContent 854753281.mraw -->

{{PageTree|content-title={{FULLPAGENAME}}}}
__NOTOC__

 <!-- From bodyContent 854327297.mraw -->

{{PanelStart
|bgColor = #DEEBFF
}}

The ''Marketing SOP'' section provides clear, standardized procedures for all marketing activities within the company.

It serves as a central reference for workflows, best practices, approval steps, and quality standards—ensuring that every campaign, asset, and communication is consistent, efficient, and aligned with our brand strategy.

Use this space to quickly access guidelines that help streamline collaboration, reduce ambiguity, and support high‑quality execution across the entire marketing team.

{{PanelEnd}}

{{SubpageList|allChildren=true|page=}}
