 <!-- From bodyContent 854949918.mraw -->

{{Info
|body = 


The “expand” macro allows to place content in a collapsible container. It replaces the macros “details” and “detailssummary”. Content is collapsed by default.

}}
{{ExpandStart
|title = Missing &quot;details&quot; macro
|breakoutWidth = 760
}}

The Details macro not appearing in Confluence Cloud is usually not a bug—it's almost always because the page is using the ''n''ew editor, where the old “Details” macro no longer exists. Confluence Cloud replaced it with the '''Expand''' macro, which provides the same functionality. This is the most common reason users in Cloud environments can’t find it.

{{ExpandEnd}}{{ExpandStart
|title = uniCon Spain 2026
|breakoutWidth = 760
}}[[File:Migration_expand-b65a385e-c137-4b29-bafe-8700c38ebae7.jpg|156px|left]]

'''uniCon Spain 2026''' is a fictional next‑generation technology fair imagined to take place in '''Madrid in October 2026''', bringing together innovators, startups, researchers, and global tech companies. Designed as a forward‑looking showcase, the event focuses on emerging technologies shaping Europe’s digital future, including AI, robotics, cybersecurity, green tech, and immersive digital experiences.

{{ExpandEnd}}
{{AttachmentsSectionStart}}
* [[Media:Migration_expand-pexels-tahir-35138560.jpg]]

{{AttachmentsSectionEnd}}

__NOTOC__

